# Favorites / Watchlist Feature – Implementation Summary

Implemented a Favorites (Watchlist) feature to allow users to save and manage their preferred movies.

* Added an "Add to Favorites" button on each movie card.
* Integrated Create (Add) and Read (View) operations using API calls.
* Created a separate Favorites page using React Router for displaying saved movies.
* Implemented Delete (Remove from Favorites) functionality to remove movies from the watchlist.
* Added conditional rendering to display an empty state message when no favorite movies are available.
* Persisted favorite movie data through backend APIs and synchronized UI state accordingly.
* Added favorite count in the navigation bar that updates dynamically when movies are added or removed.
* Prevented duplicate favorites by checking existing favorite movie IDs before adding.
* Implemented toast notifications to provide user feedback for successful add, remove, and error operations.
* Used React state management (useState, useEffect) to keep the UI updated in real time.
* Designed the Favorites page with a responsive card layout for better user experience.

Concepts Used: CRUD Operations, API Integration, State Management, Conditional Rendering, Component Reusability, Routing & Navigation, and User Feedback with Toast Notifications.